comment from NAACP's Hooks.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By HOYT HARWELL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MOUNTAIN BROOK, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Bomb-sniffing dogs and dozens of police provided security today at the funeral of a federal judge killed by a parcel bomb in a wave of attacks that may have been carried out by white racists. More than 700 mourners, including Attorney General <PERSON> Dick </PERSON> <PERSON> Thornburgh </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> Director <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Sessions </PERSON>, filled a suburban church for the service in memory of <LOCATION> U.S </LOCATION>. Circuit Judge <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Vance </PERSON>. <PERSON> Vance </PERSON> was a man `` who stood up for the underdog and the oppressed,'' his friend <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Bankruptcy Judge <PERSON> Clifford </PERSON> <PERSON> Fulford </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Birmingham </LOCATION> told mourners. `` No wonder his assassins could not stand such a man in their presence.'' The 58-year-old <PERSON> Vance </PERSON> was killed by a package bomb Saturday. <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> agents say the bomb and three others, including the one that killed <LOCATION> Savannah </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ga. </LOCATION>, lawyer <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Robinson </PERSON>, 42, on Monday, all bore <LOCATION> Georgia </LOCATION> return addresses or postmarks. Links to <ORGANIZATION> NAACP </ORGANIZATION> school desegregation efforts have been established in all four cases, leading investigators to speculate that a white racist group may be responsible. After police defused a bomb at an <ORGANIZATION> NAACP </ORGANIZATION> office in <LOCATION> Jacksonville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, Tuesday, the organization placed all its offices on alert. Four anonymous letters mailed in August to declare war on various federal appeals courts are being examined for clues to the bombings, <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Greg </PERSON> <PERSON> Jones </PERSON> said today in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> St. </ORGANIZ