<HEAD>Police Arrest 118, Including Three Celebrities, In Salvador Protest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGEES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Police arrested 118 people including musicians <PERSON> Kris </PERSON> <PERSON> Kristofferson </PERSON> and <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> <PERSON> Browne </PERSON> and actor <PERSON> Martin </PERSON> <PERSON> Sheen </PERSON> at a demonstration Wednesday against <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> support for <PERSON> El </PERSON> <PERSON> Salvador </PERSON>'s rightist government Those arrested were among 500 demonstrators outside the downtown federal building, where protesters have since mid-November gathered each Wednesday morning to block entrances. `` I'm opposed to <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> military aid to the -LRB- <PERSON> Alfredo </PERSON> -RRB- <PERSON> Cristiani </PERSON> government, a right-wing terror-death squad government. It has been going on for a long time,'' said <PERSON> Kristofferson </PERSON> as he sat down in front of the building. Also sitting with <PERSON> Kristofferson </PERSON> was <PERSON> Sheen </PERSON>, who has been arrested at previous demonstrations at the building. <PERSON> Browne </PERSON> was part of a group that briefly got into a shoving match with police when the group briefly blocked a federal police parking lot nearby, but returned to the federal building. `` We decided not to be arrested there because we would be arrested by city police and separated from the group,'' <PERSON> Browne </PERSON> explained. The building and its perimeter are under the jurisdiction of <LOCATION> U.S </LOCATION>. Protective Service police. Demonstrators are arrested for blocking access to a federal building, a $ 25 infraction. The demonstrations began after leftist rebels began a series of attacks against the <PERSON> Cristiani </PERSON> government beginning in mid-November. Those incidents have dwindled in recent weeks.
