<HEAD>Baker Discusses Different Supports for Democracy</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> WASHINGTON </LOCATION> -LRB- AM -RRB- _ The <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> is supporting democracy by not interfering in other countries while the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, this time, is supporting democracy by sending troops into another country, Secretary of State <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> <PERSON> III </PERSON> noted Wednesday. In discussing the Soviet criticism of the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> attack on the forces of dictator Gen. <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Antonio </PERSON> <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>, <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> said: `` Let me say that I think both the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> today are supporting democracy. At least that's what President <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON> told President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> at <LOCATION> Malta </LOCATION> when he said he had a little problem with the use of the word democratic _ I mean, ` Western values,' so we agreed that we would you use the term ` democratic values.' `` The difference is that the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> supports democracy by staying out of countries and thus permitting democracy to proceed. In this one and very unique instance, the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> did it by going in to assist a democratically elected government against a dictator.'' There have been many reports from Eastern <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> crediting <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON>'s refusal to support local Communist parties for the dramatic emergence of non-Communist governments in several capitals. <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> overturned the results of an election this year in which <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> citizens voted for <PERSON> Guillermo </PERSON> <PERSON> Endara </PERSON> for president on May 7. Noriega-formed `` Di