cent higher with March at $ 1.53 a bushel; soybeans were 1 cent lower to 1 \ cents higher with January at $ 5.78 a Cattle futures were mixed while pork futures were lower in early trading on the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. Pork belly futures were down sharply amid speculation that Thursday's weekly <ORGANIZATION> USDA </ORGANIZATION> cold storage report would show a higher-than-normal net increase last month in supplies of frozen bellies. Live cattle futures were .02 cent to .15 cent lower with December at 78.90 cents a pound; feeder cattle were .10 cent lower to .20 cent higher with January at 84.52 cents a pound; live hogs were .10 cent to .50 cent lower with December at 53.35 cents a pound; frozen pork bellies were .80 cent to 1.25 cent lower with February at 50.35 cents a pound. Livestock and meat futures settled mixed on Tuesday.
