RGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Worth </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION>, based in <LOCATION> Houston </LOCATION>, said the deal would pump $ 349 million into <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>, which is struggling to emerge from bankruptcy court protection next year. <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION>, which is selling is Miami-London route, will realize $ 102.5 million; System One, <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION>'s computer reservations system, will net $ 19.5 million through the sale of telecommunication and data processing systems needed to service the Latin American routes. `` The sale of these assets will enable <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> to continue on its course of successfully rebuilding as a smaller and stronger airline for the future, with its operations centered at its <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION> hub,'' <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> said in a statement. Eastern also said it would sell the 14 Lockheed-1011s it uses on the Latin American routes. The planes, which are an older, smaller version of the widebody jet, could bring in about $ 200 million, according to analysts' estimates. American, which has spent billions this year buying new aircraft to serve its expansion plans, says it is not interested in the jets. Analysts generally applauded American's purchases of the routes. They say the carrier's expansion beyond <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> borders is necessary if it is to become a `` player'' internationally. The deals also could have the pleasant side effect of making <ORGANIZATION> AMR </ORGANIZATION> less attractive to a corporate raider by decreasing cash and depressing earnings. `` These are good long-term moves, and if they affect earnings in the short term, they can deal with that,'' said analyst <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Daugherty </PERSON> at <ORGANIZATION> Dean </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Witter </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reynolds </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. Analyst <PERSON> Helane </PERSON> <PERSON> Becker </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hutton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> sounded a warning note, however. `` I really think that you do n't necessarily want to take $ 500 million or $ 200 million cash and give it to a competitor that would be out of business in a year,'' she said, referring to Eastern and <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION>. `` You sort of have to wonder if they could buy these assets out of bankruptcy at a cheaper price than they're doing today.'' <ORGANIZATION> AMR </ORGANIZATION> shares closed Tuesday at $ 60, up $ 2.75, in <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> trading. American has been expanding vigorously this year, buying airplanes to fly its newly acquired, or sought-after routes; beginning work on a $ 400 million maintenance facility; expanding domestic operations; and fighting off a takeover from billionaire <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Trump </PERSON>. American has broadened its European service significantly this year, and already has approval for more routes next year, when it will reach about 165 flights weekly to 18 <LOCATION> European </LOCATION> cities. Six years ago, it flew to none. Expansion also is under way in the <LOCATION> Pacific </LOCATION>, where American next year will begin flying to <LOCATION> Sydney </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Auckland </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Zealand </LOCATION>. The airline also is trying to add a second <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> flight. The growth has been financed through record profits, although <PERSON> Crandall </PERSON> has warned the performance wo n't continue this quarter or next year.
