David </PERSON> <PERSON> Townsend </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Hillsborough </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION> spokesman. If the offer is not accepted, <PERSON> Hillsborough </PERSON> faces the prospect of having to repay its notes in full, which it told bondholders at a meeting Tuesday that it could not do. <PERSON> Hillsborough </PERSON>'s financial problems began last summer when it was named in the class-action lawsuit. Because of the suit, <ORGANIZATION> Kohlberg </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kravis </ORGANIZATION> has been unable to sell off <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Walter </PERSON>'s assets. And without the proceeds from the sales, the company can not meet its upcoming debt payments.
