<HEAD>Orange Juice Futures Climb Higher On Freeze Fears</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DAVID DISHNEAU</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Orange juice futures prices climbed higher Wednesday on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cotton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> as fears of a weekend freeze in the <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> citrus belt intensified. On other commodity markets, sugar futures fell sharply; coffee futures gained in reaction to the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> military action in <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION>; precious metals advanced; energy futures were mixed; grains and soybeans fell; and livestock and meat futures retreated. Futures prices for frozen concentrated orange juice settled 1.9 cents to 3.05 cents higher with the contract for delivery in January up 2 cents at $ 1.3445 a pound. Freezing temperatures are almost certain to reach <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>'s citrus region this weekend as one of the most powerful cold-air masses of the decade lumbers down from <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION>, said <PERSON> Jon </PERSON> <PERSON> Davis </PERSON>, a meteorologist who tracks the impact of the weather on commodities for <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hutton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> `` This air mass is so strong that even the fringe of it has potential to cause some damage across the citrus belt,'' <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> said `` Now it's just a matter of how much damage.'' The coldest temperatures, ranging from the lower 20s in the northern reaches of the fruit region to the lower 30s in the south, are expected on Friday night and Saturday night, <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> said. With temperatures that cold for an extended period, he said, trees could be damaged as well as fruit, which could cut into production for years to come. Sugar futures prices plunged on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Coffee </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Sugar </ORGANIZATION> <O